$ *.format.ps1xml

{ Hash tables

  It is not possible to use `*.format.ps1xml` files to customize how → Windows/PowerShell/language/type/hash-table[hash tables] are displayed.

}
{ No format.ps1xml files in PowerShell 6 and later

  Beginning in PowerShell 6, the *default views* are defined in the → Windows/PowerShell/language/object[objects's] source code.
  -
  Therefore, the `*.format.ps1xml` files from PowerShell 5.1 and earlier don't exist anymore.

? However, it is still possible to create «own» `*.format.ps1xml` files to change the display of objects.

}

sa:

  → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/typeData/types-ps1xml-format

  The → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/formatData[`formatData`] command noun.
